metadata.synopsis: A masculine woman (Angela Pleasence) invites another woman (Lorna Heilbron) up to her house in the country and stabs her.

reviews: Fans of vintage atmospheric horror films featuring unhinged, emotionally damaged women should definitely enjoy Angela Pleasance in this resurrected gem, even if they know what to expect.
Symptoms seems to amplify its sense of suffocation, of desperation, and its sense of doomed inevitability.
Symptoms is ultimately, as its title implies, a psychodramatic study of repressed sexuality and confounded identity.
